ZH: 他总是幸灾乐祸地笑着，看到别人遭遇不幸就感到高兴。
EN: He always smiles with schadenfreude, feeling happy when others encounter misfortune.

ZH: 她对同事的失败感到幸灾乐祸，表现出极其不友好的态度。
EN: She takes pleasure in her colleague's failure, showing an extremely unfriendly attitude.

ZH: 这种幸灾乐祸的心态不能带来长久的快乐。
EN: This schadenfreude mentality does not bring long-lasting happiness.

ZH: 他的幸灾乐祸让他的朋友们感到厌倦。
EN: His schadenfreude makes his friends feel disgusted.

ZH: 那个羡慕嫉妒恨的人总是满足于幸灾乐祸。
EN: The person full of envy and hatred is always satisfied with schadenfreude.

ZH: 这种幸灾乐祸的态度没有什么道德感。
EN: This schadenfreude attitude lacks moral sense.

ZH: 心地不善的人总是幸灾乐祸地看着别人受难。
EN: People with wicked hearts always look with schadenfreude as others suffer.

ZH: 别让幸灾乐祸的心态毒害你的内心，保持善良和仁慈。
EN: Don't let the mentality of schadenfreude poison your heart, stay kind and compassionate.

ZH: 对他人遭遇不幸并不应该带来幸灾乐祸的快感。
EN: Taking pleasure in others' misfortune should not bring schadenfreude.

ZH: 幸灾乐祸的人很少会被认为善良和仁慈。
EN: People with schadenfreude are rarely considered kind and compassionate.

ZH: 这位领导总是以幸灾乐祸的方式对待下属，让整个团队感到不安。
EN: The leader always treats subordinates with a schadenfreude attitude, making the whole team feel uneasy.

ZH: 幸灾乐祸的人终将以孤独收场。
EN: People with schadenfreude will ultimately end up alone.

ZH: 在困难时相互帮助比幸灾乐祸更重要。
EN: Helping each other in difficult times is more important than schadenfreude.

ZH: 幸灾乐祸并不能带来真正的快乐，只能给自己招来更多的痛苦。
EN: Schadenfreude does not bring real happiness, only more pain to oneself.

ZH: 被幸灾乐祸心态毒害的人最终会沦为群众唾弃的对象。
EN: People who are poisoned by the mentality of schadenfreude will eventually become objects of public contempt.

ZH: 用幸灾乐祸来对待别人只会导致自己的孤独与痛苦。
EN: Treating others with schadenfreude will only lead to one's own loneliness and suffering.

ZH: 对人的遭遇感到幸灾乐祸并不是一种美德。
EN: Taking pleasure in others' misfortune is not a virtue.

ZH: 幸灾乐祸只会让人们看到你的丑陋和狭隘。
EN: Schadenfreude will only show people your ugliness and narrowness.

ZH: 在别人遭遇不幸时，我们应该给予同情而不是幸灾乐祸。
EN: When others encounter misfortune, we should show sympathy instead of schadenfreude. 

ZH: 他总是暗自幸灾乐祸地看着别人失败。
EN: He always secretly enjoys watching others fail.
